'''Croatian Minute Movie Cup''' ({{lang-hr|Hrvatski festival jednominutnih filmova}}) is the longest running international [[film festival]] in [[Croatia]], held every year in [[Požega, Croatia|Požega]]. The festival began in 1993.

Between 1993, when the festival began, and 2015, more than 5000 films from 79 countries were submitted.

