The '''Emily Dickinson International Society''' ('''EDIS''') is an international organisation relating to American poet [[Emily Dickinson]] (1830–1886). It was founded in 1988 and its aim is to "Promote, perpetuate and enhance the study and appreciation of Emily Dickinson worldwide".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uia.org/s/or/en/1100065872|title=Emily Dickinson International Society|work=Open Yearbook: a service of the UIA|publisher=Union of International Associations|accessdate=24 December 2013}}</ref>

The society publishes ''[[The Emily Dickinson Journal]]'' (ISSN 1059-6879) twice yearly<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.emilydickinsoninternationalsociety.org/node/16|title=Journal|publisher=EDIS|accessdate=24 December 2013}}</ref>  and, for members, ''The Emily Dickinson International Society Bulletin'' (ISSN 1055-3932).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.emilydickinsoninternationalsociety.org/node/17|title=Bulletin|publisher=EDIS|accessdate=24 December 2013}}</ref> It holds an Annual Meeting and "EDIS Institute" meetings. Every two or three years it holds an International Conference. These have taken place in the USA (1992), Austria (1995), USA (1998), Norway (2001), Hawaii (2004), Japan (2007), England (2010) and the 2014 event is planned for the USA.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.emilydickinsoninternationalsociety.org/node/14|title=International Conferences|date=EDIS|accessdate=24 December 2013}}</ref>

The society is affiliated to the [[American Literature Association]] (ALA), "a Coalition of Societies Devoted to the Study of American Authors"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://americanliteratureassociation.org/directories/directory-of-scholars-2/ala-societies-a-e/|title=ALA societies A-E|publisher=American Literature Association|accessdate=24 December 2013}}</ref>  and is sponsoring two sessions at the 2014 ALA Annual Conference.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://call-for-papers.sas.upenn.edu/node/53244|title=Emily Dickinson International Society at ALA 2014|work=cfp.english.upenn.edu|publisher=University of Pennsylvania: Department of English|accessdate=24 December 2013}}</ref>

An Emily Dickinson Society had been formed in Japan in 1980, eight years before the foundation of EDIS.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Mitchell|first1=Domhnall|last2=Stuart|first2=Maria|title=The International Reception of Emily Dickinson|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0Ohpauju-7IC&lpg=PA4&dq=%22Emily%20dickinson%20international%20society%22&pg=PA4#v=onepage&q=%22Emily%20dickinson%20international%20society%22&f=false|accessdate=24 December 2013|series=Continuum Reception Studies|year=2009|publisher=Continuum|isbn=9780826497154|page=4|chapter=Introduction: Emily Dickinson abroad}}</ref>

