{{Infobox prepared food | name = Giouvetsi | image = Giouvetsi.JPG | image_size = 250px | caption = | alternate_name = Youvetsi | country = [[Greece]] | region = | creator = | course = [[Pasta]] | type = | served = | main_ingredient = [[Meat]] ([[Chicken (food)|chicken]], [[Lamb and mutton|lamb]] or [[beef]]), [[pasta]], [[tomato sauce]] (with [[cinnamon]] or [[bay leaves]]) | variations = | calories = | other = }}
'''Giouvetsi''' or '''Youvetsi''' ({{IPA-el|ʝuˈvet͜si|pron}}, from [[Turkish language]] ''güveç'') is a baked [[Greek cuisine|Greek]] dish made with [[Chicken (food)|chicken]], [[Lamb and mutton|lamb]] or [[beef]] and pasta, either ''kritharaki'' ([[Orzo (pasta)|orzo]]) or ''[[hilopites]]'' (small square noodles), and tomato sauce (usually spiced with [[allspice]] and sometimes [[cinnamon]], [[cloves]] or [[bay leaves]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wisegeek.com/what-is-giouvetsi.htm|title=What Is Giouvetsi? (with pictures)|publisher=}}</ref>. Other common ingredients include onions/[[shallots]], garlic, [[beef stock]], and red wine, as well as some cheese to serve.
