{{Infobox ethnic group | group = Ivorians in France | pop = 450,000 (Estimated) | popplace = [[Paris]], [[Marseille]], [[Toulouse]], [[Lyon]] , [[Bordeaux]] | langs = [[French language|French]], [[Languages of Ivory Coast|Ivorian languages]] | rels = [[Islam]], [[Christianity]], [[animism]] | related = [[Black people in France]], [[Afro-French]] }} '''Ivorians in France''' consist of migrants from [[Côte d'Ivoire]] and their descendants living and working in France. They are one of the [[diaspora]]s from [[Black Africa]] in France.
== History == Prior to 1990, immigration from the Ivory Coast to France was very limited. It was mostly students and businessmen who wanted to return to [[Côte d'Ivoire]].<ref>http://www.letelegramme.com/ig/generales/france-monde/france/qui-sont-les-ivoiriens-de-france-23-01-2011-1183500.php</ref> But with the economic crisis and the politic instability of their home country, many chose to remain in France and the Ivorian population increased.
