'''Mobaye Mbanga Airport''' {{Airport codes||FEFE}} is an airport serving [[Mobaye]], a town on the [[Ubangi River]] in the [[Basse-Kotto]] prefecture of the [[Central African Republic]].
The airport is {{convert|7|km}} downstream from the town, and south approach and departure might cross the river, which is locally the border with the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].
The Gbadolite [[non-directional beacon]] (Ident: '''BLT''') is located {{convert|6.8|nmi|km|1}} southwest of the airport. The Gbadolite [[VOR-DME]] (Ident: '''BLT''') is located {{convert|12.5|nmi|km|1}} southwest of the airport.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ourairports.com/navaids/BLT/Gbadolite_NDB_CD/|title=Gbadolite NDB (BLT) @ OurAirports|website=ourairports.com|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ourairports.com/navaids/BLT/Gbadolite_VOR-DME_CD/|title=Gbadolite VOR-DME (BLT) @ OurAirports|website=ourairports.com|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref>
