'''Mongolian cattle''' are a cattle breed native to [[Mongolia]] and [[Inner Mongolia]]. In 1949, Mongolian cattle began to be improved with crossbreeding to European breeds. 

Mongolian cattle have been herded for centuries by [[nomad]]s and are highly valued for their meat.<ref>[http://www.thecattlesite.com/breeds/beef/28/mongolian/overview The Cattle Site - Breeds]</ref><ref>[http://www.ansi.okstate.edu/breeds/cattle/mongolian/index.htm Oklamhoma State University - Mongolian cattle] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101229203157/http://www.ansi.okstate.edu/breeds/cattle/mongolian/index.htm |date=2010-12-29 }}</ref>

In 2008, 40,000 of the breed died due to harsh winter conditions.<ref>[http://www.mongolia-web.com/economy/1628-news-report-40000-mongolian-cattle-dead-due-to-harsh-winter Mongolia Web -News Report] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150419031024/http://www.mongolia-web.com/economy/1628-news-report-40000-mongolian-cattle-dead-due-to-harsh-winter |date=2015-04-19 }}</ref>

