{{Italic title}} {{taxobox | image = Scalibregma inflatum (Rathke, 1843).JPG | image_caption = ''S. inflatum'' under stereo microscope | name = ''Scalibregma inflatum'' | regnum = [[Animalia]] | phylum = [[Annelida]] |classis=[[Polychaeta]] | familia = [[Scalibregmatidae]] | familia_authority = Malmgren, 1867 | genus = ''[[Scalibregma]]'' | genus_authority = Rathke, 1843 | species = ''''' S. inflatum ''''' | binomial = ''Scalibregma inflatum'' | binomial_authority = [[Martin Rathke|Rathke]], 1843 }}
'''''Scalibregma inflatum''''', also known as T headed worm, is a burrowing marine [[polychaete]]. It is a cosmopolitan species that can be found from the Arctic to Antarctica, although most probably several species are confounded.<ref>{{cite journal |author= Bakken, T. |author2=E. Oug |author3=J.A. Kongsrud |title=Occurrence and distribution of ''Pseudoscalibregma'' and ''Scalibregma'' (Annelida, Scalibregmatidae) in the deep Nordic Seas, with the description of ''Scalibregma hanseni'' |journal=Zootaxa|volume=3753 |issue=2 |pages=101–117 |year=2014|doi=10.11646/zootaxa.3753.2.1}}</ref>
==Morphology==
Up to 6&nbsp;cm long with an orange body with 50–60 segments. Body is composed of a wide anterior part of segments 15–17 and a long slim posterior part. Prostomium rectangular shaped with two lateral horns making it appear as a ''T. peristomium'' without chaetae. Parapodia small and oval at first increasing in size from segments 16–18. Four pairs of branching gills dorsally on 2-5 segment with chaetae.<ref name=DKfauna>{{cite book |author=Kirkegaard, J. B. |title=Havbørsteorme II|series=Danmarks Fauna |volume=86 |pages=241–242 |year=1996|doi=}}</ref><ref name=MarineFauna>{{cite book |author1=Hayward, P. J. |author2=Ryland, J. S. |lastauthoramp=yes |title=Handbook of the Marine Fauna of North-West Europe|publisher=Oxford University Press |page=224 |year=1995|doi=}}</ref>
==Ecology==
Mainly found in muddy substrate, but can also be found in sand and between stones and shells. ''S. inflatum'' is a deposit feeder. During the spawning period ''S. inflatum'' undergoe [[epitoky]].<ref name=DKfauna /><ref name=MarineFauna />
==Systematics== ''Scalibregma inflatum'' is found within the polychaete family [[Scalibregmatidae]].<ref name=WoRMS>{{cite WoRMS |author= Bellan, G. |year=2008 |title=''Scalibregma inflatum'' Rathke, 1843 |id=130980 |accessdate=22 December 2016 |db=Polychaeta}}</ref> The genus ''Scalibregma'' is composed of 15 different species.<ref>{{cite WoRMS |author= Bellan, G. |year=2008 |title=''Scalibregma'' Rathke, 1843 |id=129555 |accessdate=22 December 2016 |db=Polychaeta}}</ref>
